  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F.",
    "Thaw and drain spinach, then press between layers of paper towels or cheese cloth to remove excess moisture.",
    "Drain and chop artichoke hearts.",
    "In a large bowl, combine spinach, artichoke hearts, cream cheese, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, garlic, and lemon juice, stirring well.",
    "Spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1-1/2 inch baking dish and sprinkle with breadcrumbs.",
    "Bake at 375°F for 25 minutes.",
    "Serve warm with assorted crackers or bread."
